  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Administration of intravascular fluids is one of the methods to prevent SA-induced&#xD;
      hypotension, but empirical intraoperative volume repletion carries the risk of fluid overload&#xD;
      during elective surgery. Over fluid resuscitation is associated with organ dysfunction and&#xD;
      higher mortality rate , thus, to avoid ineffective or even harmful intravascular volume&#xD;
      expansion, it is important to have tools to predict hypotension and fluid responsiveness.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
